.TH REXIT 1 "January 2025" "rexit 1.1.6" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
rexit \- A rice-ready TUI power menu for Linux with multi-WM support
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rexit
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B rexit
is a lightweight, terminal-based power menu designed for Linux systems.
It provides a clean interface to quickly execute common power management
commands with support for multiple window managers including Hyprland,
Sway, i3, BSPWM, and AwesomeWM.
.PP
Features include:
.IP \[bu] 2
Clean TUI interface built with Ratatui
.IP \[bu] 2
Keyboard and mouse navigation
.IP \[bu] 2
Background animations with performance monitoring
.IP \[bu] 2
Theme support with customizable colors
.IP \[bu] 2
Responsive layout adapting to terminal size
.IP \[bu] 2
Emoji fallback for terminals without Nerd Fonts
.IP \[bu] 2
Grace period for critical actions
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-init
Generate a default configuration file at
.BR ~/.config/rexit/config.toml
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-config " " \fIPATH\fR
Use a custom configuration file from the specified path
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-theme " " \fINAME\fR
Load a theme from
.BR ~/.config/rexit/themes/<name>.toml
.TP
.BR \-\-list\-themes
List all available themes in the themes directory
.TP
.BR \-\-check\-config
Validate the configuration file and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-emoji
Use emoji icons instead of Nerd Fonts
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print help information
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print version information
.SH KEYBOARD CONTROLS
.SS Navigation
.TP
.BR "Up/k"
Move selection up
.TP
.BR "Down/j"
Move selection down
.TP
.BR "Enter"
Execute selected command
.TP
.BR "Esc/q"
Cancel and exit
.SS Action Shortcuts
Each action has its own configurable shortcut key:
.TP
.BR s
Shutdown
.TP
.BR r
Reboot
.TP
.BR u
Suspend
.TP
.BR l
Lock
.TP
.BR o
Logout
.TP
.BR c
Cancel
.SS Hidden Features
.TP
.BR a
Open animation selector menu
.TP
.BR "Konami Code"
Enter the Konami code (up up down down left right left right b a) to enable rainbow mode
.SH MOUSE SUPPORT
rexit supports mouse input in terminals that support it:
.IP \[bu] 2
Left-click on an action to select and execute it
.IP \[bu] 2
Scroll up/down to navigate through actions
.IP \[bu] 2
Click anywhere to cancel confirmation or grace period
.SH CONFIGURATION
Configuration is stored in
.BR ~/.config/rexit/config.toml .
All fields are optional, and defaults will be used for missing values.
.SS Basic Options
.TP
.BR title
Window title shown in the border (default: " rexit ")
.TP
.BR title_alignment
Title alignment: "left", "center", or "right" (default: "center")
.TP
.BR layout_mode
Layout mode: "vertical", "horizontal", "grid", or "compact" (default: "vertical")
.TP
.BR wm_type
Window manager: "auto", "hyprland", "sway", "i3", "bspwm", or "awesome" (default: "auto")
.SS Colors Section
.TP
.BR foreground
Default text color
.TP
.BR background
Background color
.TP
.BR border
Border color
.TP
.BR selected_fg
Selected item text color
.TP
.BR selected_bg
Selected item background color
.TP
.BR selected_modifier
Text modifiers for selected items: "bold", "italic", "underlined"
.TP
.BR icon_color
Action icon color
.SS Animation Section
.TP
.BR enabled
Enable background animation (default: true)
.TP
.BR animation_type
Type of animation: "matrix", "rain", "snow", "stars", "fireflies", etc.
.TP
.BR speed_ms
Animation speed in milliseconds (default: 80)
.TP
.BR adaptive_quality
Reduce quality under high CPU load (default: true)
.TP
.BR min_speed_ms
Minimum animation speed in degraded mode (default: 200)
.SS Responsive Section
.TP
.BR enabled
Enable responsive layout adjustments (default: true)
.TP
.BR compact_threshold
Switch to compact layout below this width (default: 80)
.TP
.BR minimal_threshold
Switch to minimal layout below this width (default: 40)
.SH THEMES
Themes are stored in
.BR ~/.config/rexit/themes/
as TOML files. A theme file contains color, border, and animation settings.
.PP
Example theme structure:
.PP
.nf
[colors]
foreground = "#f8f8f2"
background = "#282a36"
border = "#bd93f9"

[border]
enabled = true
style = "rounded"

[animation]
animation_type = "matrix"
speed_ms = 80
color = "#50fa7b"
.fi
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.BR REXIT_USE_EMOJI
Set to "1" or "true" to force emoji icons instead of Nerd Fonts
.TP
.BR HYPRLAND_INSTANCE_SIGNATURE
Used for automatic Hyprland detection
.TP
.BR SWAYSOCK
Used for automatic Sway detection
.TP
.BR XDG_SESSION_DESKTOP
Used for window manager detection
.SH FILES
.TP
.BR ~/.config/rexit/config.toml
Main configuration file
.TP
.BR ~/.config/rexit/themes/
Directory containing theme files
.TP
.BR ~/.config/rexit/last_executed
Stores the last executed action for persistence
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Launch rexit with default settings:
.PP
.nf
$ rexit
.fi
.PP
Generate default configuration:
.PP
.nf
$ rexit --init
.fi
.PP
Use a specific theme:
.PP
.nf
$ rexit --theme dracula
.fi
.PP
Use emoji icons:
.PP
.nf
$ rexit --emoji
.fi
.PP
Validate configuration:
.PP
.nf
$ rexit --check-config
.fi
.PP
List available themes:
.PP
.nf
$ rexit --list-themes
.fi
